Celebrated Tanzanian artiste Christina Shusho will perform at a sold-out gospel concert in Kisumu on Monday. Top Kenyan artistes Everlyne Wanjiru and Evelyn Muthoka, among others, are also lined up to perform. The concert that will be held on New Year's eve, will be staged at Jomo Kenyatta Sports Ground. This will be the first time for Kisumu to host a big gospel concert and that will bring on board top hitmakers. The gospel extravaganza is scheduled to begin from 6pm till dawn. Organisers will be marking the 14th edition of the event which will also double up as a thanksgiving. Click here for the latest political news 